	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Something about the formatting of the Wiki's front page causes it to render severely messed up in Google Chrome (Chromium 13.0.782.107 on Gentoo).
<br />
<br /><img src="http://static.karatorian.org/images/temp/nesdev-wiki-chrome-thumb.png" alt="Image" />
<br /><a href="http://static.karatorian.org/images/temp/nesdev-wiki-chrome.png" class="postlink">Full Size Screenshot</a>
<br />
<br />There is a similar issue in Firefox (3.6.17), but it's not as bad. I get the feeling the box sizes are hard coded in absolute values somewhere, but I haven't dug into the CSS to check for sure.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://static.karatorian.org/images/temp/nesdev-wiki-firefox-thumb.png" alt="Image" />
<br /><a href="http://static.karatorian.org/images/temp/nesdev-wiki-firefox.png" class="postlink">Full Size Screenshot</a>
<br />
<br />I was initially going to mention this on the discussion page, but I don't have edit permissions.

		

